    {
      "id": 1,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "",
      "transparent": true,
      "gridPos": { "x": 0, "y": 0, "w": 24, "h": 6 },
      "options": {
        "mode": "html",
        "content": "<div style='padding:24px 28px;border-radius:14px;background:linear-gradient(135deg,#0b1d3a 0%,#142d5c 45%,#1e4d8c 100%);color:#f3f6fb;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08)'>\n  <div style='display:flex;align-items:baseline;gap:18px;flex-wrap:wrap'>\n    <h1 style='margin:0;font-size:38px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1px'>AIDRA</h1>\n    <span style='font-size:15px;color:#9ec1ff;font-weight:500'>Artificial Intelligence In-orbit Data pRocessing Assessment</span>\n  </div>\n  <p style='margin:10px 0 16px;font-size:16px;line-height:1.55;color:#dde6f3;max-width:980px'>\n    Feasibility study on running <b>AI-driven vessel detection</b> directly on-board a satellite, using <b>Sentinel-1 SAR</b> and the constraints of space-grade compute. End-to-end pipeline, hardware-profile benchmarking, full SHA256 traceability, AI Act conformance and autonomous re-tasking — all running on a single OCI ARM Free Tier instance in Frankfurt (EU).\n  </p>\n  <div style='display:flex;gap:8px;flex-wrap:wrap'>\n    <span style='padding:5px 11px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(46,204,113,0.18);color:#7ee2a8;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;border:1px solid rgba(46,204,113,0.35)'>● LIVE</span>\n    <span style='padding:5px 11px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(52,152,219,0.18);color:#84baef;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;border:1px solid rgba(52,152,219,0.35)'>EU-only data residency</span>\n    <span style='padding:5px 11px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(155,89,182,0.18);color:#c293e0;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;border:1px solid rgba(155,89,182,0.35)'>Reg. (EU) 2024/1689 — AI Act</span>\n    <span style='padding:5px 11px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(241,196,15,0.18);color:#f3d76b;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;border:1px solid rgba(241,196,15,0.35)'>SatCen tender SATCEN/2026/OP/0003</span>\n    <span style='padding:5px 11px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(231,76,60,0.18);color:#f0907f;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;border:1px solid rgba(231,76,60,0.35)'>OCI ARM A1 · 4 OCPU · 24 GB</span>\n  </div>\n</div>"
      }
    },

    {
      "id": 2,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "",
      "transparent": true,
      "gridPos": { "x": 0, "y": 6, "w": 24, "h": 6 },
      "options": {
        "mode": "html",
        "content": "<div style='display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:14px;padding:4px 2px'>\n  <div style='padding:18px 20px;border-radius:12px;background:#111922;border:1px solid #2b3645'>\n    <div style='font-size:11px;color:#7ea0c4;letter-spacing:2px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:8px'>WHAT</div>\n    <div style='font-size:14px;line-height:1.55;color:#dde6f3'>\n      A working proof-of-concept that runs <b>YOLOv8 + CFAR ensemble</b> on Sentinel-1 GRD scenes, geolocates each vessel, and persists every artifact with a SHA256 chain — under five hardware constraint profiles that simulate real on-orbit compute.\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <div style='padding:18px 20px;border-radius:12px;background:#111922;border:1px solid #2b3645'>\n    <div style='font-size:11px;color:#7ea0c4;letter-spacing:2px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:8px'>WHY</div>\n    <div style='font-size:14px;line-height:1.55;color:#dde6f3'>\n      Earth-observation downlink is the choke point of maritime surveillance. Doing inference <b>before</b> the bits leave orbit cuts latency from hours to minutes and bandwidth by orders of magnitude — but only if the model still fits on space-grade silicon.\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <div style='padding:18px 20px;border-radius:12px;background:#111922;border:1px solid #2b3645'>\n    <div style='font-size:11px;color:#7ea0c4;letter-spacing:2px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:8px'>HOW</div>\n    <div style='font-size:14px;line-height:1.55;color:#dde6f3'>\n      Quantization, pruning and knowledge distillation, evaluated as <b>{baseline, variant, profile}</b> triplets. Every run is reproducible from a pinned seed, an image hash, a model hash and an input-params hash — bundled into the D3 evidence package the tender expects.\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>"
      }
    },

